column3427: Daniel started having infantile spasms at 12 mos treated with Phenobarbital until he was 3. Then stopped w/o seizures for 2 yrs and was Dx West Syndrome, tried several drugs mentioned but improved greatly with Valproic Acid/Mysoline, then this med was discontinued in the country and had horrible seizures since we stopped it at once. Then he received Tegretol and this combination Valpron/Tegretol has kept seizures under control, except for some eventual episodes over the last 5 yrs. Currently is having problems with ranges over the accepted ranks and started to diminish dose. Currently takes Valpron 2 tab AM and 2 tab PM.. Tegretol 2 am- 1 noon - 2 pm> We think it is too much but don;t know how to reduce doses without causing recurrence of seizures. Very complicated for us and keeps us worried because we cannot find the medicines here in Venezuela, due to the emergency situation that we are going through. We need help.

column3427: Psychiatric  medication  had  a  terrible  effect  on  him.   He  never  restored  normal  sleep  patterns  and  never  recovered  from  constant  fatigue. He  had  no  previous  problems   besides  mild  autism  and  she  said  even   though  he  has  no  visibly  pervasive   symptoms  that  Fluoxetine  could  improve   his  autism.   Fluoxetine  caused  sleep  problems  so  she  perscribed  Clonidine.   Clonidine  caused  behavioral  problems  due  to  him  being  unable  to  sleep.   Then  he  was  prescribed  Risperidone  and  had  to  temporarily  stop  attending  public  school  due  to  seizures  when  he  had  never  before  had  seizures  in  his  life  and  was  unable  to  do  simple  math. She   then  prescribed  Amitriptelene   and  he   became  violent  when  he  had  never  done   so  before.
